    <h2>What can I find on this page?</h2>

    <p>A Project Trip Generation Screening Assessment (or a Level 1 Assessment) determines the number of person trips by mode of transportation, as well as vehicle trips, expected to be generated by the proposed project during the peak analysis hours. This assessment is one part of the two-tiered screening process to determine whether a quantified analysis of any technical areas of the transportation system (traffic, transit, pedestrians, parking) is necessary.</p>
    <br>
    <p>At this time, CEQR App automates the Project Trip Generation Screening Assessment for Residential and Office Land Uses. This page provides data, based on DOT survey data and approved past project data, necessary for Project Trip Generation Screen Assessments for the following additional Land Uses:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Hotel</li>
      <li>Local Retail</li>
      <li>Medical Office</li>
    </ul>
    <br>
    <h4>Note:</h4>
    <p>As always, this data provides the best baseline data available for the land uses specified, but does not override subsequent guidance from the Department of Transportation and from the Department of City Planning. Different data may be appropriate, based on the specific location or type of project.</p>

